  Locus:
    Page: 495
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Words
---
A physician is not angry at the intemperance of a mad patient, nor does he
take it ill to be insulted by a man in fever. Just so, should a wise man
treat all mankind as a physician treats a patient, and look upon it only as
sick and irresponsible.
